<br>
Root mob.<br>
Snare mob.<br>
Nuke mob. (eventually root will break).<br>
Run for about 5 seconds.<br>
Stop and nuke again.<br>
Repeat until mob dead.<br>
---avoid kiting creatures that are casters until you are proficient, even then be careful---<br>
<br>
Once you get proficient at learning the length of time to run before you stop and nuke again, you can just skip the root step.  Once you are proficient at root/nuke and snare/nuke (kiting) tactics you can look into Area of effect kiting.<br>
<br>
On a side note, I highly recommend you complete the Staff of Temperate Flux quest from the Temple of Solusek Ro.  The staff is, in my opinion, a must-have wizard item.  Over the course of 60 levels, my flux staff, epic, and jboots have (by far) been my &quot;most used&quot; items.  The flux staff will give you a mana free method of pulling mobs at long range that has the nice side effect of lowering the mobs resistances (fire, cold) a little bit.<br>
<br>
If you need any help with the quest you can find the information on eqmaps, graffes, and most quest websites because the quest has been around forever.  Shoot me a tell online if you need help 'whacking' any of the creatures needed for the staff, if I am not busy I would be happy to give you a hand.<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
<br>
<br>
-Braken<br>
